ENTRY       EC 1.14.13.128              Enzyme
NAME        7-methylxanthine demethylase;
            ndmC (gene name)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With NADH or NADPH as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into the other donor
SYSNAME     7-methylxanthine:oxygen oxidoreductase (demethylating)
REACTION    7-methylxanthine + O2 + NAD(P)H + H+ = xanthine + NAD(P)+ + H2O + formaldehyde [RN:R07965 R07966]
ALL_REAC    R07965 R07966
SUBSTRATE   7-methylxanthine [CPD:C16353];
            O2 [CPD:C00007];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
PRODUCT     xanthine [CPD:C00385];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H2O [CPD:C00001];
            formaldehyde [CPD:C00067]
COMMENT     A non-heme iron oxygenase. The enzyme from the bacterium Pseudomonas putida prefers NADH over NADPH. The enzyme is specific for 7-methylxanthine [2]. Forms part of the caffeine degradation pathway.
